**Claim:** Government and law are distinct subjects, both crucial for informed citizenship but covering different material.
**Purpose:** attack => A basic understanding of the law should be mandatory in schools.;attack => Current government courses often neglect the judicial branch.;attack => Most people will interact with the legal system at some point.;attack => Mandatory legal education equips citizens to navigate their own lives effectively within a legal framework.;
**Content:** The proposition that government and law should be interchangeable is flawed.  While both are crucial for informed citizenship and should be core classes, they cover distinct material.  Government focuses on the workings of our political system, while law examines the legal processes and rights guaranteed to every citizen, as outlined, for example, on the US Constitution website.  Making both mandatory ensures Americans understand both their government and their rights under the law.
